Kenya's Kibiwott Kandie has won silver in the World Half Marathon men's race coming second after Uganda's Jacob Kiplimo. Kandie finished at 58:54 while Kiplimo finished the race in 58:49 minutes in Poland. "We feel very great and we are very happy. I am happy that I have broken the record. The course was really good I really, " Kiplimo said. Amedework Walelegn of Ethiopia came in third to win bronze in 59:08. He was followed by Joshua Cheptegei who was surprisingly beaten into 4th in 59:21. More to follow